    "description": "The strategy is a systematic value and income tilt within large cap US equities, designed to exploit the historical tendency for high dividend yield Dow constituents to mean revert as pessimism fades. Each year it starts from the Dow 30 (proxied via DIA constituents), ranks members by dividend yield, selects the 10 highest yielding names (Dogs of the Dow), then further concentrates into the five lowest priced among those (the Puppies), targeting potential re-rating and dividend carry in beaten down blue chips.\n\nPortfolio construction is long only and equal weighted across the five selected stocks, rebalanced annually at the start of each calendar year using fundamental dividend yield and price data. Names must have price above 5 and positive dividend yield to be eligible. The primary risk control is concentration capped by fixed breadth (five holdings) and equal weight sizing; turnover is limited to once per year. There are no explicit drawdown, volatility, or stop-loss overlays, so realized risk is primarily driven by equity market beta and single-name idiosyncratic exposure within the concentrated basket.",
